1
00:00:33,458 --> 00:00:37,083
[SUBARU] Why me?
How did all this happen?

2
00:00:38,958 --> 00:00:41,875
[barking]

3
00:00:41,958 --> 00:00:44,458
[barking, meowing, chirping]

4
00:00:46,458 --> 00:00:49,750
I've clearly made
the worst decision of my life!

5
00:00:49,833 --> 00:00:51,875
[squawking]

6
00:02:22,875 --> 00:02:24,958
[birds chirping]

7
00:02:26,041 --> 00:02:27,625
Hmm.

8
00:02:31,166 --> 00:02:33,708
Hey.
Could you please move?

9
00:02:36,125 --> 00:02:39,791
Why would you sleep
on my laptop, of all places?

10
00:02:39,875 --> 00:02:42,583
I can't get any work
done like this!

11
00:02:42,666 --> 00:02:46,000
Dammit. Guess I'll have
to move you myself.

12
00:02:49,041 --> 00:02:51,208
It's like a barnacle!

13
00:03:00,666 --> 00:03:02,916
Why won't you move?

14
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:06,708
Oh, I know.
I'll tempt it with cat food.

15
00:03:09,083 --> 00:03:11,208
Well, this sucks.

16
00:03:11,291 --> 00:03:14,166
I forgot I gave it the last
of the food yesterday.

17
00:03:15,291 --> 00:03:17,416
I've gotta have something.

18
00:03:22,250 --> 00:03:24,208
[groans]

19
00:03:25,875 --> 00:03:28,416
I'll order more.
If I do it online...

20
00:03:30,708 --> 00:03:32,416
But I can't!

21
00:03:33,416 --> 00:03:37,000
Oh! I'll just do it
from the browser on my phone.

22
00:03:40,250 --> 00:03:43,708
What? I don't have two
to three business days!

23
00:03:43,791 --> 00:03:46,541
What do I do?
Ugh.

24
00:03:46,625 --> 00:03:49,125
Guess I'll have to go
buy it in person.

25
00:03:49,208 --> 00:03:51,250
No, no, no!
I don't want to go outside,

26
00:03:51,333 --> 00:03:53,666
or worse,
have to deal with people!

27
00:03:53,750 --> 00:03:55,541
But the cat food.

28
00:03:55,625 --> 00:03:58,000
But having to deal
with the outside world!

29
00:03:58,083 --> 00:04:00,458
[groans]

30
00:04:09,625 --> 00:04:11,250
They're out.

31
00:04:13,833 --> 00:04:16,000
Here's what I'll do.

32
00:04:16,083 --> 00:04:18,791
I'll give it bread for now.
Cats eat bread, don't they?

33
00:04:25,083 --> 00:04:27,333
Hang on!
I think I heard somewhere

34
00:04:27,416 --> 00:04:29,916
that it's bad
to give cats human food.

35
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:33,875
But there was no cat food.
Where else could I buy some?

36
00:04:37,250 --> 00:04:40,041
Is that place a pet store?

37
00:04:42,125 --> 00:04:44,708
What a relief!
I can't believe my luck!

38
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:58,166
Worst idea ever.

39
00:04:58,250 --> 00:05:00,750
[barking]

40
00:05:07,625 --> 00:05:09,583
I've spent my life
avoiding contact

41
00:05:09,666 --> 00:05:11,416
with any sort
of living thing.

42
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:14,375
This place is the polar opposite
of everything I believe in.

43
00:05:14,458 --> 00:05:16,708
-[barks]
-[panicked yelling]

44
00:05:16,791 --> 00:05:19,708
[SUBARU grunting, panting]

45
00:05:21,166 --> 00:05:23,916
Get in, get out,
nobody gets hurt.

46
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:28,083
Cat food!
And more cat food.

47
00:05:28,166 --> 00:05:29,666
So much cat food.

48
00:05:30,916 --> 00:05:34,083
-Which one's right?
-[beeping]

49
00:05:34,166 --> 00:05:36,541
What the heck
is the difference?

50
00:05:36,625 --> 00:05:39,333
[NANA]
You finding everything okay?

51
00:05:39,416 --> 00:05:41,208
Is there something
I can help you with?

52
00:05:41,291 --> 00:05:44,916
Oh, crap!
A human is trying to talk to me!

53
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:48,291
Um... Um...
I just need cat food.

54
00:05:48,375 --> 00:05:51,458
Great! Shopping for
a little kitty-cat!

55
00:05:51,541 --> 00:05:54,833
I love cats. I'll help you.
What's the name?

56
00:05:58,333 --> 00:06:00,000
[exclaims]

57
00:06:00,083 --> 00:06:01,708
What is this?

58
00:06:01,791 --> 00:06:04,458
Do pet shops require you
to give them your name?

59
00:06:06,416 --> 00:06:10,291
-Subaru Mikazuki.
-Well, that is adorable!

60
00:06:10,375 --> 00:06:14,208
-How demeaning!
-And what about the age?

61
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:19,375
-Twenty-three years old?
-Wow! Quite the senior citizen!

62
00:06:19,458 --> 00:06:21,208
What kind of world
do we live in that

63
00:06:21,291 --> 00:06:24,125
twenty-somethings
are considered old people?

64
00:06:24,208 --> 00:06:26,500
I wanna go home.

65
00:06:28,291 --> 00:06:31,041
Thanks for being patient
with all the questions.

66
00:06:31,125 --> 00:06:33,625
They just help me narrow down
the options a bit,

67
00:06:33,708 --> 00:06:35,958
to get you the product
fits your needs the best!

68
00:06:36,041 --> 00:06:39,000
-[SUBARU] Huh?
-Here, take these free samples.

69
00:06:39,083 --> 00:06:41,583
You can try them out
before you buy, if you'd like.

70
00:06:41,666 --> 00:06:43,833
I'm sorry.
I have to eat these?

71
00:06:43,916 --> 00:06:46,333
[NANA] Of course not!
They're for Subaru!

72
00:06:46,416 --> 00:06:48,625
Huh?

73
00:06:48,708 --> 00:06:53,250
Huh?
Wait, I'm confused.

74
00:06:53,333 --> 00:06:55,250
I thought you meant
Subaru was your cat,

75
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:57,333
but now it seems like...

76
00:06:57,416 --> 00:07:03,250
...that's your name.
And, you're twenty-three?

77
00:07:05,083 --> 00:07:07,833
Oh, I'm sorry!
This is so embarrassing!

78
00:07:07,916 --> 00:07:09,875
I should have been much clearer!

79
00:07:09,958 --> 00:07:11,541
[SUBARU]
I want to disappear.

80
00:07:11,625 --> 00:07:15,666
So, um...
Listen, let's start over.

81
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:18,333
Want to tell me your cat's name?

82
00:07:18,416 --> 00:07:20,375
[SUBARU]
I haven't given it one.

83
00:07:20,458 --> 00:07:24,250
Oh, really? Well, doesn't that
make things more difficult?

84
00:07:25,958 --> 00:07:27,625
[SUBARU]
I don't think so.

85
00:07:27,708 --> 00:07:29,875
It comes to me
without being called.

86
00:07:29,958 --> 00:07:31,583
Oh, no, I mean,

87
00:07:31,666 --> 00:07:34,791
when you take it to its vet
check-ups and things like that.

88
00:07:34,875 --> 00:07:38,000
Not to mention, you two do live
in the same house, after all.

89
00:07:38,083 --> 00:07:41,500
You two are family.
So, please,

90
00:07:41,583 --> 00:07:44,250
think about giving kitty
a name, okay?

91
00:07:44,333 --> 00:07:45,666
It's for the best.

92
00:07:47,291 --> 00:07:49,000
Oh, also, if it's young,

93
00:07:49,083 --> 00:07:50,791
this food will be
a better choice for it.

94
00:07:50,875 --> 00:07:52,208
Okay?

95
00:07:53,583 --> 00:07:55,791
[SUBARU]
Yeah. I have to go!

96
00:07:55,875 --> 00:07:58,541
Thanks, and good luck
with everything.

97
00:07:58,625 --> 00:08:02,208
Hi. It's your favorite
editor, Kawase.

98
00:08:02,291 --> 00:08:04,541
Sorry to bug you,
but can you chat for a sec?

99
00:08:04,625 --> 00:08:07,500
[SUBARU panting]

100
00:08:07,583 --> 00:08:09,083
[SUBARU]
Yes. What is it?

101
00:08:09,166 --> 00:08:11,041
What's happening now?
Are you all right?

102
00:08:11,125 --> 00:08:12,916
[panting]

103
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:15,166
Yes. I'm fine. What's up?

104
00:08:15,250 --> 00:08:17,083
[KAWASE]
Oh. Good. Uh...

105
00:08:17,166 --> 00:08:21,166
It's nothing urgent, really,
I just wanted to let you know.

106
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:25,125
Um, the response
to your new book has been great!

107
00:08:25,208 --> 00:08:28,041
I just couldn't wait
to tell you.

108
00:08:28,125 --> 00:08:29,916
Oh. I see.

109
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:32,708
[KAWASE]
Uh, by the way, Mikazuki,

110
00:08:32,791 --> 00:08:36,041
have you thought of a name
for the cat yet?

111
00:08:36,125 --> 00:08:37,541
[SUBARU]
What the hell?

112
00:08:37,625 --> 00:08:39,708
Everyone's on my case
about that!

113
00:08:39,791 --> 00:08:42,583
Why do I have to
give it a name at all?

114
00:08:42,666 --> 00:08:45,500
[KAWASE] Uh, look, man,
you sure there's nothing wrong?

115
00:08:45,583 --> 00:08:47,125
Please calm down.

116
00:08:49,166 --> 00:08:52,583
[KAWASE]
Hey. Mikazuki?

117
00:08:52,666 --> 00:08:54,583
[SUBARU] I should have just
ordered it online

118
00:08:54,666 --> 00:08:56,083
like I wanted to.

119
00:08:56,166 --> 00:08:58,458
Then I wouldn't have had
to go out in public.

120
00:08:58,541 --> 00:09:00,583
And this wouldn't
have happened.

121
00:09:00,666 --> 00:09:02,125
[KAWASE]
Uh, anyway,

122
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:04,125
we've gotten lots
of fan letters.

123
00:09:04,208 --> 00:09:07,083
Everybody's dying to know
what the cat's name is.

124
00:09:07,166 --> 00:09:08,416
[SUBARU]
Oh, wait.

125
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:10,458
He was talking about
the cat in the story?

126
00:09:10,541 --> 00:09:13,750
-[KAWASE] You still there?
-[SUBARU] I'm listening.

127
00:09:13,833 --> 00:09:16,291
[KAWASE] Giving the cat a name
would definitely make readers

128
00:09:16,375 --> 00:09:18,041
feel more attached to it.

129
00:09:18,125 --> 00:09:20,625
So, just give it
some thought, okay?

130
00:09:20,708 --> 00:09:22,250
Yeah, sure.

131
00:09:25,875 --> 00:09:27,750
A name, huh?

132
00:09:30,958 --> 00:09:34,041
[HIROTO] Yo, Subaru!
Are you at home?

133
00:09:35,583 --> 00:09:37,750
-Well, that's rare.
-[barking]

134
00:09:39,583 --> 00:09:42,916
Hey, Taro.
Are you being a good boy?

135
00:09:50,458 --> 00:09:52,166
There we go.

136
00:09:54,916 --> 00:09:58,625
Seriously, does this guy
ever shop? Oh!

137
00:10:09,500 --> 00:10:12,083
That should do it. Good.

138
00:10:13,375 --> 00:10:15,291
Mom always cooks too much.

139
00:10:15,375 --> 00:10:18,125
Subaru should be all set
for a while with this, though.

140
00:10:19,875 --> 00:10:21,875
-Oh! Oh!
-[hissing]

141
00:10:21,958 --> 00:10:25,458
What?
Hey! Come back!

142
00:10:25,541 --> 00:10:27,208
Hmm.

143
00:10:27,291 --> 00:10:29,916
Man, what was
the cat's name again?

144
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:33,208
Meh, whatever.
I'll ask Subaru next time.

145
00:10:33,291 --> 00:10:36,083
[birds chirping]

146
00:10:36,166 --> 00:10:38,500
[SUBARU]
I get that fans ask questions.

147
00:10:38,583 --> 00:10:40,208
But, still...

148
00:10:40,291 --> 00:10:42,625
[WOMAN]
Hi, Koro. How are you today?

149
00:10:42,708 --> 00:10:43,958
[dog barking]

150
00:10:44,041 --> 00:10:46,000
She's always so spirited!

151
00:10:46,083 --> 00:10:47,708
That's the truth.

152
00:10:47,791 --> 00:10:50,708
Sometimes I wish she could be
as quiet as her sister, Berry.

153
00:10:50,791 --> 00:10:53,416
[SUBARU]
The harsh reality is...

154
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:56,666
I don't have anybody
to call by name anymore.

155
00:10:56,750 --> 00:11:00,375
I'd prefer not to talk
to anyone, though, honestly.

156
00:11:00,458 --> 00:11:04,291
And calling out to a creature
that can't understand me...

157
00:11:04,375 --> 00:11:07,000
[BOY]
Go get it, Ryutaro!

158
00:11:07,083 --> 00:11:09,000
[BOY laughs]

159
00:11:09,083 --> 00:11:11,250
Over here!

160
00:11:11,333 --> 00:11:13,250
What's the point?

161
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:16,291
All right! You're the best dog
in the world, Ryutaro!

162
00:11:16,375 --> 00:11:18,166
[laughing]

163
00:11:18,250 --> 00:11:21,666
-Okay, let's go home!
-[barking]

164
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:23,500
[door closes]

165
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:33,708
It's gone. Where'd it go?

166
00:11:36,125 --> 00:11:39,083
Oh, well.
Time to get to work.

167
00:11:43,333 --> 00:11:46,083
[scratching]

168
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:51,833
[panting]

169
00:12:01,583 --> 00:12:04,208
[typing]

170
00:12:15,166 --> 00:12:18,125
I thought I had some other
reference books over here.

171
00:12:20,375 --> 00:12:22,458
[hissing]

172
00:12:24,291 --> 00:12:27,916
How can anything sleep
in such a tight space?

173
00:12:29,875 --> 00:12:33,458
What are you even thinking, cat?
Come on.

174
00:12:34,708 --> 00:12:37,125
A name, huh?

175
00:12:37,208 --> 00:12:41,208
I don't see how giving you one
would change anything.

176
00:12:41,291 --> 00:12:44,541
Maybe thinking of a name
for my character will help.

177
00:12:44,625 --> 00:12:47,333
I might stumble
across one for you, too.

178
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:50,833
That said, I'm a writer.

179
00:12:50,916 --> 00:12:53,000
I can't just throw names
around arbitrarily

180
00:12:53,083 --> 00:12:55,583
without giving them
serious thought.

181
00:12:56,625 --> 00:12:59,541
Each name has to represent
the individual.

182
00:12:59,625 --> 00:13:01,875
It has to fit their personality.

183
00:13:03,875 --> 00:13:06,125
A cat's personality?

184
00:13:11,125 --> 00:13:13,833
It's just a cat.

185
00:13:14,875 --> 00:13:18,083
It's no use! I got nothing!

186
00:13:18,166 --> 00:13:19,833
Hold on.

187
00:13:19,916 --> 00:13:22,541
Why don't I just let it
choose its own name?

188
00:13:22,625 --> 00:13:24,916
I'll see if it responds
to anything.

189
00:13:26,291 --> 00:13:31,833
A... Amane.
E... Enishi.

190
00:13:31,916 --> 00:13:35,416
I... Iroha.

191
00:13:36,666 --> 00:13:39,333
U... Uguisu.

192
00:13:40,625 --> 00:13:42,916
Ogi?

193
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:49,291
Kasane. Kinu.
Kurumi. Keshi.

194
00:13:55,625 --> 00:13:58,333
Ryu. Ruri.

195
00:14:00,083 --> 00:14:02,125
Not a single response.

196
00:14:02,208 --> 00:14:06,500
What the heck am I doing?
This is stupid.

197
00:14:06,583 --> 00:14:08,541
-Wakaba--
-[thwacking]

198
00:14:08,625 --> 00:14:10,333
[SUBARU grunts]

199
00:14:12,916 --> 00:14:16,458
I'm an idiot.
I'm getting nowhere.

200
00:14:16,541 --> 00:14:18,666
Which tells me something.

201
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:22,166
Neither people nor animals
want anything to do with me.

202
00:14:27,250 --> 00:14:31,458
Hey, Mom! Mom!
Will you read this?

203
00:14:31,541 --> 00:14:35,041
[SUBARU'S MOM] Oh, again?
You must really love this book.

204
00:14:36,916 --> 00:14:39,458
"Then the crescent moon said,

205
00:14:39,541 --> 00:14:41,750
"'It looks like
the sun is awake.

206
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:44,666
'So, it's time for me
go to sleep.'"

207
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:47,875
Crescent moon?
Isn't that what our name means?

208
00:14:47,958 --> 00:14:49,708
[SUBARU'S MOM laughs]
That's right.

209
00:14:49,791 --> 00:14:53,083
Yeah, but, the crescent
moon went to sleep.

210
00:14:53,166 --> 00:14:55,708
I want the crescent moon to be
up in the sky all the time.

211
00:14:55,791 --> 00:14:59,833
Really? But you sleep
at night, too, don't you?

212
00:14:59,916 --> 00:15:01,916
Well, the moon has to sleep.

213
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:05,500
The moon's out at night,
and the sun's out all day.

214
00:15:05,583 --> 00:15:09,750
They like to work together,
to light the whole world's way.

215
00:15:09,833 --> 00:15:11,833
[SUBARU]
Are the sun and moon friends?

216
00:15:11,916 --> 00:15:14,708
[SUBARU'S MOM]
Of course. Very good friends.

217
00:15:14,791 --> 00:15:18,208
And they're important
to each other.

218
00:15:18,291 --> 00:15:24,250
The sun in spring.
Spring. “Haru.”

219
00:15:25,791 --> 00:15:27,333
Haru.

220
00:15:29,625 --> 00:15:31,041
Haru?

221
00:15:31,125 --> 00:15:32,791
[meows]

222
00:15:36,541 --> 00:15:40,000
Wait.
Did it just respond to that?

223
00:15:40,083 --> 00:15:41,333
“Haru”?

224
00:15:43,541 --> 00:15:45,375
Crap! The food!

225
00:15:45,458 --> 00:15:47,375
I completely forgot
about feeding it!

226
00:15:47,458 --> 00:15:49,416
Thank goodness
for free samples.

227
00:15:51,458 --> 00:15:53,000
I'm awful.

228
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:56,041
What kind of owner deprives
his cat of food like that?

229
00:16:00,041 --> 00:16:04,125
I told you.
We don't have any more of that.

230
00:16:04,208 --> 00:16:07,833
I'll go buy some.
But you'll have to wait.

231
00:16:09,708 --> 00:16:12,458
So, just hang out here
and be good.

232
00:16:12,541 --> 00:16:14,833
-Haru.
-[meows]

233
00:16:18,416 --> 00:16:21,291
It's not like the cat
can understand me, right?

234
00:16:21,375 --> 00:16:23,791
I must be losing my mind.

235
00:16:23,875 --> 00:16:26,583
Talking to a cat.
I mean, who does that?

236
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:31,000
[NANA] You two do live
in the same house, after all.

237
00:16:31,083 --> 00:16:32,791
You two are family.

238
00:16:44,208 --> 00:16:48,791
[HARU] “Haru."
I know that word. I like it.

239
00:16:48,875 --> 00:16:52,000
It sounds so nice and warm.

240
00:16:56,750 --> 00:17:02,916
I've made a great discovery.
I love lying in this spot.

241
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:06,541
It always feels
so cozy right here.

242
00:17:06,625 --> 00:17:11,250
I think it's my favorite place,
especially for taking naps.

243
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:14,583
[gasps]

244
00:17:14,666 --> 00:17:17,041
What's this?
What's going on?

245
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:21,291
I found this spot first,
stinky human.

246
00:17:21,375 --> 00:17:25,125
Leave me alone!
I'm never gonna let you have it!

247
00:17:32,125 --> 00:17:34,333
Ha. I won.

248
00:17:37,625 --> 00:17:39,708
-[barking outside]
-[door rattling]

249
00:17:39,791 --> 00:17:43,125
What is that?
It's so loud.

250
00:17:45,458 --> 00:17:49,541
Aw, this thing this gets cold
fast when it makes that noise.

251
00:17:49,625 --> 00:17:53,666
But that's fine.
I was getting hungry, anyway.

252
00:17:55,583 --> 00:17:57,916
I love this life.

253
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:00,708
I can eat whenever
I start feeling hungry now!

254
00:18:00,791 --> 00:18:02,666
This is the best!

255
00:18:05,791 --> 00:18:08,666
No food?

256
00:18:08,750 --> 00:18:11,625
-[HIROTO] Seriously...
-[HARU] Wh-- What's that?

257
00:18:11,708 --> 00:18:13,541
[HIROTO]
Oh!

258
00:18:18,458 --> 00:18:21,625
[HIROTO]
Mom always cooks too much.

259
00:18:21,708 --> 00:18:24,416
Subaru should be all set
for a while with this, though.

260
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:26,250
Oh! Oh!

261
00:18:26,333 --> 00:18:27,791
Oh, no!

262
00:18:27,875 --> 00:18:29,958
[panicked screaming]

263
00:18:32,958 --> 00:18:35,416
Why was he here?
He's always eating!

264
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:38,083
Did he eat all my food, too?

265
00:18:38,166 --> 00:18:40,333
I got careless.

266
00:18:41,750 --> 00:18:44,666
I was dumb to assume
I could eat whenever I wanted.

267
00:18:44,750 --> 00:18:47,875
Took it for granted that
there'd always be food for me.

268
00:18:47,958 --> 00:18:50,041
I should've known.

269
00:18:52,708 --> 00:18:54,666
But, now it's gone.

270
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:58,875
I'm so hungry.

271
00:19:04,875 --> 00:19:08,875
[GIRL] Hi, kitty!
I was hoping I'd see you again!

272
00:19:08,958 --> 00:19:11,125
Wait here. I'll be right back!

273
00:19:11,208 --> 00:19:14,041
-Here you go!
-[HARU whimpering]

274
00:19:14,125 --> 00:19:16,083
Make sure it's not
too hot to eat.

275
00:19:16,166 --> 00:19:19,000
-Haru.
-Sure seems cool enough to me.

276
00:19:20,791 --> 00:19:24,041
[GIRL] Doesn't Haru's mom
make the tastiest food?

277
00:19:24,125 --> 00:19:27,208
-[HARU] Haru?
-[GIRL] I love her cooking, too!

278
00:19:28,541 --> 00:19:31,750
-[HARU] Does “Haru” mean “food”?
-You know what?

279
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:34,833
Watching the kitty eat is
making me want something, too!

280
00:19:34,916 --> 00:19:38,416
What am I going
to do with you?

281
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:43,458
[HARU] Haru. Haru.
I like it.

282
00:19:43,541 --> 00:19:45,958
It sounds so nice and warm.

283
00:19:49,791 --> 00:19:52,333
-[shrieking]
-[SUBARU gasps]

284
00:19:53,916 --> 00:19:56,500
That scared me!
What's your problem?

285
00:19:56,583 --> 00:19:59,250
Why do you want
to take my spots?

286
00:19:59,333 --> 00:20:02,166
Well, you can't have
this one, either!

287
00:20:03,375 --> 00:20:07,208
-[SUBARU] Ryu. Ruri.
-[HARU] Ugh.

288
00:20:07,291 --> 00:20:10,166
What's that human
mumbling about over there?

289
00:20:10,250 --> 00:20:13,291
-[SUBARU] Wakaba.
-[HARU] Shut up!

290
00:20:16,041 --> 00:20:20,291
Hey, that worked.
Now it's peaceful and quiet.

291
00:20:20,375 --> 00:20:25,500
-What a relief.
-[SUBARU] Haru. Haru.

292
00:20:29,208 --> 00:20:34,333
Hey, it's that word.
The one with the warm sounds.

293
00:20:37,208 --> 00:20:38,750
Haru?

294
00:20:38,833 --> 00:20:41,333
Food! Ah!

295
00:20:46,166 --> 00:20:47,291
Ah!

296
00:20:47,375 --> 00:20:51,291
He's got it!
Food! Food!

297
00:20:51,375 --> 00:20:54,250
[eager whimpering]

298
00:20:54,333 --> 00:20:58,000
I knew it!
It does mean “food”!

299
00:20:58,083 --> 00:21:00,375
[puzzled whimpers]

300
00:21:01,541 --> 00:21:03,875
Gone already?

301
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:08,333
Hey, human!
There's no more food!

302
00:21:08,416 --> 00:21:11,708
Can you bring me some more?
Please?

303
00:21:12,708 --> 00:21:16,416
Okay. So just hang out here
and be good, Haru.

304
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:19,708
Yeah! “Haru.”
Haru's what I want!

305
00:21:19,791 --> 00:21:20,958
[meows]

306
00:21:21,041 --> 00:21:23,333
I know what that word means!

307
00:21:23,416 --> 00:21:25,916
It means that food
is coming, right?

308
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:33,250
[bell tolls]

309
00:21:33,333 --> 00:21:36,291
What? Where'd he-- ?

310
00:21:36,375 --> 00:21:38,541
Where's the... food?

311
00:21:42,125 --> 00:21:47,541
I don't understand.
Why is that human so confusing?

312
00:23:19,166 --> 00:23:21,750
[SUBARU]
Hey. Where'd you go?

313
00:23:21,833 --> 00:23:25,041
I got you some more food.

314
00:23:25,125 --> 00:23:27,041
-Haru!
-[food clinking in bowl]

315
00:23:28,958 --> 00:23:32,541
[HARU]
Food! More food!

316
00:23:32,625 --> 00:23:35,666
[WOMAN ON TV] My shoulders,
they've been so tight lately.

317
00:23:35,750 --> 00:23:39,250
I know what you need!
Stick on one of these!

318
00:23:39,333 --> 00:23:42,041
Haru Stick-Ons!

319
00:23:42,125 --> 00:23:44,166
Ow, my sciatica.

320
00:23:44,250 --> 00:23:47,166
-[MAN ON TV] Slap it on! Haru!
-[HARU yells]

321
00:23:48,583 --> 00:23:51,916
-[MAN ON TV] Haru Stick-Ons!
-Where's the food?

322
00:23:53,125 --> 00:23:56,958
-What's the matter with you?
-Food!

323
00:23:57,041 --> 00:23:59,458
[MAN 2] Hey, can you say
“Haru” ten times, fast?

324
00:23:59,541 --> 00:24:01,125
[WOMAN 2]
Haru, Haru, Haru, Haru, Haru,

325
00:24:01,208 --> 00:24:03,166
Haru, Haru, Haru,
Haru, Haru!

326
00:24:03,250 --> 00:24:05,666
-That made me hungry.
-[MAN 2] Yeah, same here.

